The paper focuses on manipulation planning for household objects, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The approach is based on deep neural networks, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors use point-cloud and natural language data, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses pre-training and fine-tuning methods, which are common in deep learning (cs.LG).
